WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.251 --> 00:00:03.462
[waves crashing]

2
00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:07.132
[wind howling]

3
00:00:08.467 --> 00:00:10.219
[Sarah breathing heavily]

4
00:00:12.346 --> 00:00:13.805
[grunts]

5
00:00:20.270 --> 00:00:22.563
[breathing heavily]

6
00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:23.565
[grunts]

7
00:00:29.321 --> 00:00:30.405
Be not afraid.

8
00:00:31.448 --> 00:00:33.032
[Thomas] What's happening to me?

9
00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:35.035
[unsettling music playing]

10
00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:41.874
- [Holyoke] I can't see anything.
- Oh. God.

11
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:44.293
[Thomas coughs]

12
00:00:44.294 --> 00:00:46.171
[Frances shrieks]

13
00:00:47.548 --> 00:00:51.592
- [breathing heavily]
- [Cromwell coughs]

14
00:00:51.593 --> 00:00:53.846
Frances. Frances!

15
00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:55.931
Frances!

16
00:00:57.140 --> 00:00:58.600
- Frances!
- [Frances inhales sharply]

17
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:02.729
- Frances?
- [Frances] Help!

18
00:01:03.438 --> 00:01:04.772
- [Sarah] Frances!
- [Frances coughs]

19
00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:06.607
[Sarah] Frances!

20
00:01:06.608 --> 00:01:09.527
[coughing continues]

21
00:01:09.528 --> 00:01:11.070
[grunts]

22
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:12.072
Grab hold!

23
00:01:15.701 --> 00:01:17.368
[Frances gasping]

24
00:01:17.369 --> 00:01:19.496
- [Sarah] Grab ahold.
- [Frances breathes heavily]

25
00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:25.334
[breathes heavily]

26
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:28.255
[Sarah] Hold on. I'm-I'm trying. Frances!

27
00:01:29.298 --> 00:01:30.548
Don't let go!

28
00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:34.052
[Sarah coughs. speaks indistinctly]

29
00:01:47.357 --> 00:01:50.360
[unsettling music continues]

30
00:01:55.449 --> 00:01:57.284
[thunder crashes]

31
00:02:09.253 --> 00:02:11.256
[music fades]

32
00:02:12.341 --> 00:02:14.092
You have to sound the siren. Tom.

33
00:02:15.344 --> 00:02:16.553
[townsperson] She's right.

34
00:02:17.095 --> 00:02:19.014
Those thunderheads ain't natural.

35
00:02:19.681 --> 00:02:22.726
Read the accounts of the Storm of 1783.

36
00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:27.147
Started with big. ugly
storm clouds just like that.

37
00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:31.318
Storm roared in like The Great Flood.

38
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:35.279
Storm brought waterspouts and tornadoes.

39
00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:38.199
Men were ripped up into the black sky.

40
00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:41.161
Babies torn from their mothers' arms.

41
00:02:43.121 --> 00:02:44.748
[electricity buzzing]

42
00:02:57.469 --> 00:03:00.681
- [exhales deeply]
- [line rings]

43
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:03.600
How we looking?

44
00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:05.644
[person] <i>You got your Doppler up?</i>

45
00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:07.437
Yeah.

46
00:03:09.773 --> 00:03:11.650
[sighs] <i>It doesn't look great</i>.

47
00:03:13.151 --> 00:03:14.902
What's the mainland saying?

48
00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:17.906
<i>We lost contact with the mainland
20 minutes ago.</i>

49
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:22.870
Okay. Well. then keep me updated.

50
00:03:30.043 --> 00:03:31.169
You have to sound the siren.

51
00:03:31.170 --> 00:03:33.172
You have to get everyone
into the shelters.

52
00:03:35.382 --> 00:03:37.134
Right now. it's just a storm.

53
00:03:39.595 --> 00:03:44.182
If I… If I sound the siren.
that's all they'll say when they get home.

54
00:03:44.183 --> 00:03:47.853
They went to Widow's Bay
and ended up in a fucking storm shelter.

55
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:50.897
That doesn't happen
on Martha's Vineyard. [sighs]

56
00:03:50.898 --> 00:03:52.316
At least they'll get back home.

57
00:03:53.817 --> 00:03:55.152
People have died. Tom.

58
00:04:03.202 --> 00:04:04.203
[grunts]

59
00:04:06.747 --> 00:04:07.748
[huffs]

60
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:10.250
[exhales deeply]

61
00:04:12.794 --> 00:04:14.046
[inhales deeply]

62
00:04:14.796 --> 00:04:16.130
[exhales deeply]

63
00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:20.719
[breathes heavily]

64
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:23.722
[exhales deeply]

65
00:04:30.062 --> 00:04:32.272
[huffs]

66
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:36.067
- [huffs] Fuck.
- [Patricia] Oh. uh…

67
00:04:36.068 --> 00:04:37.194
Um…

68
00:04:37.945 --> 00:04:39.863
Shit. Shit. Shit.

69
00:04:40.364 --> 00:04:41.447
[huffs]

70
00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.075
[grunts] Fuck. [grunts]

71
00:04:43.825 --> 00:04:46.702
- [grunting]
- [Patricia] Uh… Tom!

72
00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:48.455
- [Tom huffs]
- Oh. my God.

73
00:04:50.415 --> 00:04:51.499
- You okay?
- No.

74
00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:53.710
My back. [straining] Can't move it.

75
00:04:54.545 --> 00:04:55.711
She's missing a finger.

76
00:04:55.712 --> 00:04:56.755
[straining] What?

77
00:04:57.798 --> 00:05:01.008
[wheezing] No. Patricia.
Patricia. Patricia.

78
00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:02.302
Patricia.

79
00:05:03.554 --> 00:05:06.013
- Oh. Kenny.
- [Rosemary] Everybody stay back.

80
00:05:06.014 --> 00:05:08.766
- [Tom] Oh. fuck. [grunts. groans]
- [Rosemary] Tom. what happened?

81
00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:11.477
- [Tom] Kenny.
- I said to stay back.

82
00:05:11.478 --> 00:05:14.022
- He might have broke something.
- [Tom] No. Let him help me.

83
00:05:14.565 --> 00:05:16.899
- Maybe if we both grab a side. we can--
- Back off. Kenny.

84
00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:19.068
He might have spinal damage.
Can't move him.

85
00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:21.279
I'll do it myself. Here we go.

86
00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:23.489
- No. No. [groans. grunts]
- [Rosemary] All right.

87
00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:25.700
You're pushing it down on me.
You're pushing it down on me.

88
00:05:25.701 --> 00:05:27.326
Don't speak. Tom.

89
00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:30.162
Your lungs might be collapsed.
All right. here we go. Ready?

90
00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:32.331
One. two. three.

91
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:33.833
- Ow! Oh. my sciatica.
- [Tom grunts]

92
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:35.376
- Oh. Poor Rosemary.
- [Rosemary] Shit.

93
00:05:35.377 --> 00:05:38.213
- [Dale] Oh. no.
- What? [coughing]

94
00:05:39.965 --> 00:05:42.509
[grunts. exhales deeply]

95
00:05:43.427 --> 00:05:44.970
Thanks. Kenny. [grunts]

96
00:05:45.971 --> 00:05:47.472
[Patricia] Tom. her finger.

97
00:05:48.056 --> 00:05:50.558
Look. Tom. It's missing.

98
00:05:50.559 --> 00:05:51.934
[Tom] What? [grunts]

99
00:05:51.935 --> 00:05:53.103
Frances Warren.

100
00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:56.356
Her brother ran over her ring finger.
It's in Sarah Warren's journal.

101
00:05:56.940 --> 00:05:57.941
[grunts]

102
00:05:59.401 --> 00:06:02.236
This woman in the painting.
Frances Fisher.

103
00:06:02.237 --> 00:06:04.406
mysteriously washed up on shore as a girl.

104
00:06:05.032 --> 00:06:07.116
This is Frances Warren.

105
00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:10.037
That's why Richard Warren's
bloodline didn't end with him.

106
00:06:10.746 --> 00:06:12.289
Because his daughter lived.

107
00:06:12.789 --> 00:06:14.666
[thunder crashes]

108
00:06:17.586 --> 00:06:18.587
[exhales deeply]

109
00:06:20.756 --> 00:06:21.757
Tom?

110
00:06:24.301 --> 00:06:25.302
[exhales deeply]

111
00:06:29.264 --> 00:06:30.265
[grunts]

112
00:06:34.436 --> 00:06:36.396
Tom. are you listening to me?

113
00:06:41.235 --> 00:06:42.236
[grunts]

114
00:06:44.029 --> 00:06:45.197
[clicks tongue]

115
00:06:46.365 --> 00:06:49.659
If that is Frances Warren.

116
00:06:49.660 --> 00:06:53.413
that's over 400 years
of ancestry to untangle.

117
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:57.125
Rosemary probably
already has genealogy on Barnabus.

118
00:07:00.838 --> 00:07:03.048
And then what? We round them up?

119
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:09.847
[breathes heavily]

120
00:07:11.348 --> 00:07:13.600
[exhales deeply]

121
00:07:21.233 --> 00:07:23.819
- [line rings]
- [sighs]

122
00:07:25.696 --> 00:07:27.239
[clicks tongue] This is Loftis.

123
00:07:29.867 --> 00:07:30.909
Hit the siren.

124
00:07:32.703 --> 00:07:35.121
[thunder rumbling]

125
00:07:35.122 --> 00:07:36.790
- [wind howling]
- [thunder rumbles]

126
00:07:53.307 --> 00:07:57.769
This ferry isn't coming.
and I wouldn't even get on it if it did.

127
00:07:58.979 --> 00:08:00.313
Can we please just go back home?

128
00:08:00.314 --> 00:08:03.859
No. listen. ferries operate
in storms all the time.

129
00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:08.197
[siren blaring]

130
00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:15.621
Bechir.

131
00:08:16.747 --> 00:08:17.872
get me home.

132
00:08:17.873 --> 00:08:20.124
[siren continues]

133
00:08:20.125 --> 00:08:21.710
I just need to try one more thing.

134
00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:23.378
All right? Okay.

135
00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:30.426
Stop…

136
00:08:30.427 --> 00:08:32.429
[speaking indistinctly]

137
00:08:58.455 --> 00:09:00.707
[Wyck] So. what's the plan here?

138
00:09:01.208 --> 00:09:02.835
I'm getting the fuck off this island.

139
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:05.170
I know how to operate a boat.

140
00:09:06.171 --> 00:09:07.798
Forty miles from the mainland.

141
00:09:08.465 --> 00:09:11.969
In a boat with a range of 15 miles tops
with a full tank.

142
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:16.639
And even if you do somehow refuel

143
00:09:16.640 --> 00:09:20.644
while in the middle of this storm.
the waves'll capsize you.

144
00:09:21.770 --> 00:09:23.313
I can't have my child here.

145
00:09:25.983 --> 00:09:27.150
I understand that. but…

146
00:09:27.985 --> 00:09:30.319
That boat came here on a boat.

147
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.614
Not gonna get you to the mainland in this.

148
00:09:49.798 --> 00:09:50.883
[grunts]

149
00:10:00.058 --> 00:10:01.476
What have you told her?

150
00:10:05.397 --> 00:10:06.398
Nothing.

151
00:10:08.192 --> 00:10:09.610
I can't tell her anything.

152
00:10:11.153 --> 00:10:14.323
- [dramatic music playing]
- [siren continues]

153
00:10:14.907 --> 00:10:17.618
[automated voice] <i>Attention residents
and visitors to Widow's Bay.</i>

154
00:10:18.202 --> 00:10:22.121
<i>There is a mandatory storm advisory
by order of the mayor.</i>

155
00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:24.666
<i>Report to the shelter immediately.</i>

156
00:10:25.584 --> 00:10:28.337
<i>Attention residents
and visitors to Widow's Bay…</i>

157
00:10:57.783 --> 00:11:00.077
[dramatic music continues]

158
00:11:07.209 --> 00:11:09.211
[people chattering]

159
00:11:12.798 --> 00:11:13.881
[person] Sorry.

160
00:11:13.882 --> 00:11:16.050
[Tom] All right everyone.
head towards my voice.

161
00:11:16.051 --> 00:11:18.804
Make this left. Make your way downstairs.

162
00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:22.056
Welcome to your first nor'easter. folks.

163
00:11:22.057 --> 00:11:26.353
After this. you're gonna be one of us.
A real New Englander.

164
00:11:26.979 --> 00:11:30.690
Heard it's. uh… Heard it's hitting
Martha's Vineyard pretty hard.

165
00:11:30.691 --> 00:11:33.861
Now you'll be refunded
by your accommodations for tonight.

166
00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:35.946
That money's already spent.

167
00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:38.073
- Okay.
- [music fades]

168
00:11:40.868 --> 00:11:41.869
[mouthing] Come here.

169
00:11:45.622 --> 00:11:48.791
I know. I know. I just… I had to make sure
PJ and those guys were all coming.

170
00:11:48.792 --> 00:11:51.711
Listen. I know we do this dance a lot.

171
00:11:51.712 --> 00:11:52.920
Today. please--

172
00:11:52.921 --> 00:11:54.755
- I'm not gonna go anywhere.
- Can you-- Okay.

173
00:11:54.756 --> 00:11:56.048
- I promise.
- Okay. good.

174
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:59.677
And hey. we can go
to a Sox game whenever. you know.

175
00:11:59.678 --> 00:12:01.847
I mean. they still have
half a season left. so…

176
00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:06.559
I love you. bud.

177
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:08.019
All right. go downstairs.

178
00:12:08.020 --> 00:12:09.021
Okay.

179
00:12:11.148 --> 00:12:12.608
We have an issue.

180
00:12:13.525 --> 00:12:14.943
[Kenny] Generator's out.

181
00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:19.197
The emergency lights run on batteries.
They'll last a half hour.

182
00:12:19.198 --> 00:12:21.157
then the shelter goes pitch-black.

183
00:12:21.158 --> 00:12:22.700
Oh. my God.

184
00:12:22.701 --> 00:12:24.660
There's power surges
through the whole island.

185
00:12:24.661 --> 00:12:27.038
'Cause of the storm.
it's overloading the grid.

186
00:12:27.039 --> 00:12:29.248
Even the heavy-duty gear is getting fried.

187
00:12:29.249 --> 00:12:32.126
So-So what do we do?
We have to get power down there.

188
00:12:32.127 --> 00:12:33.794
Garrett might have a replacement.

189
00:12:33.795 --> 00:12:35.797
He's got the same one
up at the lighthouse.

190
00:12:37.716 --> 00:12:39.301
- [radio beeps]
- [Tom] Garrett.

191
00:12:41.762 --> 00:12:44.138
Garrett. I'm looking right now.
I don't see you…

192
00:12:44.139 --> 00:12:45.973
Oh. oh. All right. listen. Listen to me.

193
00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:49.060
We need your starter
for the old generator.

194
00:12:49.061 --> 00:12:51.521
[Garret. distorted] <i>I can't understand
a goddamn word you're saying.</i>

195
00:12:51.522 --> 00:12:52.855
- Do--
- [feedback on radio]

196
00:12:52.856 --> 00:12:54.357
Does he not have a goddamn phone?

197
00:12:54.358 --> 00:12:56.235
- No.
- [static crackles]

198
00:12:57.653 --> 00:12:58.736
Garrett.

199
00:12:58.737 --> 00:13:01.656
[Garret. distorted] <i>How the hell am I
supposed to get you a goddamn starter?</i>

200
00:13:01.657 --> 00:13:04.075
- Garrett. Garrett. I can't hear…
- [static crackling]

201
00:13:04.076 --> 00:13:06.911
We need your starter.

202
00:13:06.912 --> 00:13:08.621
- This is an emergency.
- [feedback whining]

203
00:13:08.622 --> 00:13:11.123
- I'm going up there.
- Tom. you shouldn't go out there.

204
00:13:11.124 --> 00:13:12.416
It's not safe.

205
00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:13.836
[thunder rumbles]

206
00:13:30.894 --> 00:13:33.105
[thunderclap]

207
00:13:34.106 --> 00:13:35.691
[pants]

208
00:13:36.608 --> 00:13:37.943
[Bechir] Let's get you warm.

209
00:13:38.443 --> 00:13:40.319
- [door closes]
- Let me help you.

210
00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:41.363
- Okay.
- [Chelle groans]

211
00:13:42.865 --> 00:13:44.073
What's wrong. hon?

212
00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:46.618
Uh. maybe it's just Braxton Hicks.

213
00:13:48.412 --> 00:13:49.871
Dr. Morgan's downstairs.

214
00:13:49.872 --> 00:13:51.415
- Let's get you comfortable.
- Okay.

215
00:13:52.457 --> 00:13:53.458
[Chelle groans]

216
00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:02.842
[sighs]

217
00:14:02.843 --> 00:14:05.512
[eerie music playing]

218
00:14:31.038 --> 00:14:32.456
[music fades]

219
00:14:36.585 --> 00:14:37.628
[sighs]

220
00:14:38.462 --> 00:14:39.880
[gasps. sighs]

221
00:14:40.464 --> 00:14:42.673
You need to learn to knock. cowboy.

222
00:14:42.674 --> 00:14:44.968
This is a castle doctrine town.

223
00:14:45.469 --> 00:14:48.554
Funny to think the whole island survived

224
00:14:48.555 --> 00:14:51.391
on whale blubber
well into my father's day.

225
00:14:52.059 --> 00:14:54.269
The whaler. the captain. they…

226
00:14:54.978 --> 00:14:57.564
they owned this place. my daddy would say.

227
00:14:58.232 --> 00:15:00.067
[sighs] What's this about. Wyck?

228
00:15:05.155 --> 00:15:06.490
[sighs]

229
00:15:16.834 --> 00:15:18.835
I need you to do something for me.

230
00:15:18.836 --> 00:15:20.838
[dramatic music playing]

231
00:15:27.094 --> 00:15:29.763
[thunder rumbling]

232
00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:39.898
[radio crackling]

233
00:15:41.066 --> 00:15:43.569
[distorted music playing]

234
00:15:46.029 --> 00:15:47.780
[radio crackling]

235
00:15:47.781 --> 00:15:49.783
[distorted music playing]

236
00:15:54.162 --> 00:15:56.122
- [crackling continues]
- [hits dash]

237
00:15:56.123 --> 00:15:57.624
[distorted music stops]

238
00:16:00.460 --> 00:16:02.462
[dramatic music continues]

239
00:16:15.893 --> 00:16:18.312
[chains clinking]

240
00:16:31.241 --> 00:16:32.326
Garrett!

241
00:16:36.663 --> 00:16:37.748
Garrett!

242
00:16:40.083 --> 00:16:41.126
Fuck!

243
00:16:47.216 --> 00:16:49.384
No. No!

244
00:16:51.762 --> 00:16:52.763
Shit.

245
00:17:03.357 --> 00:17:04.358
[Tom] Garrett?

246
00:17:06.818 --> 00:17:09.445
Goddamn it. Garrett.
I came here for the starter.

247
00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:14.534
Oh! Oh. thank God!

248
00:17:14.535 --> 00:17:16.452
- [Garret] <i>I'll bring it back.</i>
- What? No. no. no!

249
00:17:16.453 --> 00:17:18.453
No. stay there. stay there!
I'm coming to you!

250
00:17:18.454 --> 00:17:21.164
[stammers] I'm coming back!
I'm coming back!

251
00:17:21.165 --> 00:17:22.751
Dale. stop him!

252
00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:26.839
[thunder rumbles]

253
00:17:32.177 --> 00:17:34.179
[wind howling]

254
00:17:41.478 --> 00:17:43.480
[music intensifies]

255
00:17:45.941 --> 00:17:47.066
Fuck. No!

256
00:17:47.067 --> 00:17:50.028
[stammers] No. no! Garrett!

257
00:17:50.529 --> 00:17:52.196
- No.
- [blares horn]

258
00:17:52.197 --> 00:17:53.990
Garrett. go!

259
00:17:53.991 --> 00:17:56.660
Go. go. go. go. go!

260
00:17:57.202 --> 00:17:59.579
Get inside! Get inside!

261
00:17:59.580 --> 00:18:01.956
- [Todd] Hey. Wyck! Hey. hey. Wyck!
- [music fades]

262
00:18:01.957 --> 00:18:03.959
- Shaman?
- Wyck!

263
00:18:04.459 --> 00:18:05.835
[Tom] Come inside!

264
00:18:05.836 --> 00:18:08.004
- Help me out!
- No. no. no! Come inside!

265
00:18:08.005 --> 00:18:10.131
- No. no. come on!
- [Todd groans]

266
00:18:10.132 --> 00:18:11.340
Help me. man!

267
00:18:11.341 --> 00:18:12.967
No. no! Leave it. leave it!

268
00:18:12.968 --> 00:18:15.636
- I need these!
- Come inside!

269
00:18:15.637 --> 00:18:18.848
[storm rumbles. howls]

270
00:18:18.849 --> 00:18:20.767
Come inside! Come inside right now!

271
00:18:21.643 --> 00:18:23.186
[Todd] Wyck!

272
00:18:23.187 --> 00:18:25.189
[screaming]

273
00:18:28.942 --> 00:18:30.944
[dramatic music playing]

274
00:18:38.035 --> 00:18:39.203
[music stops]

275
00:19:00.307 --> 00:19:01.807
No one leaves this shelter.

276
00:19:01.808 --> 00:19:03.809
Do you understand? No matter what happens.

277
00:19:03.810 --> 00:19:06.062
Ruth's not here.

278
00:19:06.063 --> 00:19:07.396
She's home.

279
00:19:07.397 --> 00:19:08.481
Alone.

280
00:19:08.482 --> 00:19:11.526
Okay. all right.
I'll-I'll-I'll figure something out.

281
00:19:11.527 --> 00:19:13.444
We won't leave her out there.

282
00:19:13.445 --> 00:19:15.989
- [thunder rumbles]
- [lights clinking]

283
00:19:20.994 --> 00:19:21.995
[Wyck] Loftis.

284
00:19:27.292 --> 00:19:29.211
There's something you both should see.

285
00:19:40.889 --> 00:19:42.099
[Tom] What is this?

286
00:19:43.141 --> 00:19:44.852
I had her run a genealogy.

287
00:19:46.520 --> 00:19:49.355
You-You-You can't be serious.
Th-This-This is…

288
00:19:49.356 --> 00:19:51.399
- Wyck. we don't have time for that.
- I had to know.

289
00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:53.192
Know what. Wyck?

290
00:19:53.193 --> 00:19:58.282
Turned out Richard Warren
has one last living descendant.

291
00:20:01.243 --> 00:20:02.244
One?

292
00:20:02.995 --> 00:20:04.078
Who is it?

293
00:20:04.079 --> 00:20:06.831
No. Don't answer that.
It doesn't matter who it is.

294
00:20:06.832 --> 00:20:09.042
- We're not--
- Who is it?

295
00:20:09.751 --> 00:20:11.502
- Have a seat.
- Goddamn it. Rosemary!

296
00:20:11.503 --> 00:20:13.380
We don't have time for this.
Tell me who it is.

297
00:20:24.600 --> 00:20:25.601
[sighs]

298
00:20:26.602 --> 00:20:28.812
Tom. you're not really
gonna listen to this.

299
00:20:41.366 --> 00:20:43.075
[Rosemary sighs]

300
00:20:43.076 --> 00:20:44.453
All right. Here we go.

301
00:20:46.622 --> 00:20:51.083
Warren and the first wife. Sybil.
lost their first two boys

302
00:20:51.084 --> 00:20:53.170
when they reached the island.

303
00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:57.965
As for the others.
didn't work out so well for them either.

304
00:20:57.966 --> 00:21:01.594
Nope. Tough break. Sorry. kid.

305
00:21:01.595 --> 00:21:03.596
Better luck next time. [sighs]

306
00:21:03.597 --> 00:21:05.933
Okay. I want you to picture this.

307
00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:10.561
You're a little girl. and your finger
gets broken off by a wagon wheel.

308
00:21:10.562 --> 00:21:13.064
Next thing you know. your dad's dead.

309
00:21:13.065 --> 00:21:15.942
and your stepmom
is taking you on an adventure.

310
00:21:15.943 --> 00:21:17.736
Destination? Hell.

311
00:21:18.403 --> 00:21:19.530
Your name?

312
00:21:20.113 --> 00:21:23.116
Frances Warren.

313
00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:25.618
Now. your siblings are dead.

314
00:21:25.619 --> 00:21:27.870
but God's finger flicks you
on the back of the head.

315
00:21:27.871 --> 00:21:29.497
and you float back to shore.

316
00:21:29.498 --> 00:21:33.125
Lucky you. Barnabus Fisher finds you
on his way back from a whaling trip.

317
00:21:33.126 --> 00:21:35.378
takes pity on you. little girl.

318
00:21:35.379 --> 00:21:38.130
Feeds you. clothes you. raises you.

319
00:21:38.131 --> 00:21:39.550
Wealthy man.

320
00:21:40.551 --> 00:21:42.261
It must be nice.

321
00:21:46.139 --> 00:21:49.685
- [coughing]
- [Rosemary sighs] All right. Where was I?

322
00:21:50.644 --> 00:21:54.689
Fast forward a few years
and you're in the bloom of youth.

323
00:21:54.690 --> 00:21:56.983
- [fan whirring]
- [sighs] No. I can't hear.

324
00:21:56.984 --> 00:21:58.902
I… I can't hear.

325
00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:01.946
[whirring stops]

326
00:22:01.947 --> 00:22:05.284
Okay. You're 14 years old.

327
00:22:05.951 --> 00:22:08.078
Barnabus starts
to look at you differently.

328
00:22:08.787 --> 00:22:11.539
He sits you down
over a cup of whale fin soup

329
00:22:11.540 --> 00:22:14.375
and he tells you
things are gonna be different.

330
00:22:14.376 --> 00:22:18.421
He's ripping pages off the calendar.
X. X. X. He's counting down.

331
00:22:18.422 --> 00:22:21.257
Get you a white dress.
takes you to the pastor who says.

332
00:22:21.258 --> 00:22:23.217
"All right. I guess."
And now you're married.

333
00:22:23.218 --> 00:22:25.178
You suffer a few miserable years.

334
00:22:25.179 --> 00:22:29.266
Barnabus drops dead.
leaving you his whaling business

335
00:22:30.642 --> 00:22:32.019
and also a son.

336
00:22:32.686 --> 00:22:35.563
Jonathan is a healthy baby boy.

337
00:22:35.564 --> 00:22:38.984
and when he grows up.
he won't be shooting blanks.

338
00:22:39.902 --> 00:22:41.403
He is a stud.

339
00:22:42.237 --> 00:22:46.699
Now. here is where we reach
a few ends that are dead.

340
00:22:46.700 --> 00:22:49.995
Dead baby. Dead baby. Lesbian.

341
00:22:50.537 --> 00:22:53.582
Sophia "The Heretic"
marries Byron Fairclough.

342
00:22:54.291 --> 00:22:57.668
These jackrabbits had six kids.

343
00:22:57.669 --> 00:23:00.630
and some of them have a few of their own.

344
00:23:00.631 --> 00:23:01.964
but you know what they say.

345
00:23:01.965 --> 00:23:04.800
"A family that swims together.
drowns together."

346
00:23:04.801 --> 00:23:07.970
And so. the inaugural swim is born.

347
00:23:07.971 --> 00:23:09.556
That's not a saying.

348
00:23:10.974 --> 00:23:13.142
Well. I guess I don't know
what I'm talking about

349
00:23:13.143 --> 00:23:14.770
and should just stop.

350
00:23:17.856 --> 00:23:19.775
- [Tom clicks tongue]
- [Rosemary exhales deeply]

351
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:22.361
I'm sorry. Please go on.

352
00:23:27.824 --> 00:23:29.159
[Rosemary clears throat]

353
00:23:30.202 --> 00:23:33.205
[Rosemary] Oh. No good news here.

354
00:23:33.747 --> 00:23:36.874
Dead baby. Dead baby. Lesbian.

355
00:23:36.875 --> 00:23:38.334
Can you please stop saying lesbian?

356
00:23:38.335 --> 00:23:40.127
I can't say that now?

357
00:23:40.128 --> 00:23:41.963
It's the way you're saying it.

358
00:23:41.964 --> 00:23:43.465
[Rosemary] Ugh. Fine.

359
00:23:43.966 --> 00:23:48.177
- Anyway. this next batch. all retards--
- Rosemary!

360
00:23:48.178 --> 00:23:50.847
- [Wyck sighs]
- Can you please just get on with it?

361
00:23:50.848 --> 00:23:51.974
Please.

362
00:23:53.392 --> 00:23:57.353
[Rosemary]
Joseph "The Faithful" has three kids.

363
00:23:57.354 --> 00:24:00.982
Rumor is. two of the siblings
took up with each other.

364
00:24:00.983 --> 00:24:03.609
which is their business
as far as I'm concerned.

365
00:24:03.610 --> 00:24:05.237
unless they have children.

366
00:24:06.405 --> 00:24:07.989
And in this case. they did.

367
00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:09.783
You can imagine how that went.

368
00:24:10.450 --> 00:24:13.703
Elizabeth spits out several kids.

369
00:24:13.704 --> 00:24:16.038
Jeremiah. Abigail. and Madorah.

370
00:24:16.039 --> 00:24:17.666
They're all tickets to nowhere.

371
00:24:18.417 --> 00:24:21.211
Oh. I could tell you their story
if-if we're not in a rush.

372
00:24:22.212 --> 00:24:23.297
[Wyck] Hmm.

373
00:24:25.465 --> 00:24:27.633
I suppose we're in a rush.

374
00:24:27.634 --> 00:24:31.679
Elizabeth's daughter. Grace.
marries Abraham Fitzgerald.

375
00:24:31.680 --> 00:24:34.933
and they have two daughters.
"The Ungrateful Hortence"…

376
00:24:35.601 --> 00:24:37.435
Things didn't turn out so well for her…

377
00:24:37.436 --> 00:24:39.645
and Anne Fitzgerald.

378
00:24:39.646 --> 00:24:41.397
She wasn't much to look at either.

379
00:24:41.398 --> 00:24:44.651
but she played her cards right. you know.
and married Hezekiah.

380
00:24:46.028 --> 00:24:51.073
Her son gives birth to Mabel.
who marries Luther Sullivan.

381
00:24:51.074 --> 00:24:54.203
And we have dead baby.

382
00:24:54.703 --> 00:24:58.372
And a daughter with
a bunch of kids who died.

383
00:24:58.373 --> 00:25:00.834
[chuckles] It's a great murder mystery.

384
00:25:01.877 --> 00:25:04.922
But I'll get on with it.
like Tom wants. [sighs]

385
00:25:05.881 --> 00:25:07.757
[whispers] It was the husband.

386
00:25:07.758 --> 00:25:09.842
- [projector sheets rustle]
- [normal] Henry.

387
00:25:09.843 --> 00:25:12.345
Henry does okay and gives birth to Ida.

388
00:25:12.346 --> 00:25:16.140
Ida and Frederick Long
give birth to Clarabell.

389
00:25:16.141 --> 00:25:17.433
I've seen her portrait.

390
00:25:17.434 --> 00:25:19.435
She thinks she's something.

391
00:25:19.436 --> 00:25:22.605
Clarabell marries Benjamin
and gives birth to Edward.

392
00:25:22.606 --> 00:25:23.649
and he's not much.

393
00:25:24.441 --> 00:25:26.360
And now we're in the 1900s. people.

394
00:25:27.694 --> 00:25:28.986
We get two brothers.

395
00:25:28.987 --> 00:25:31.697
Grant Livingston.
who tried to build a submarine.

396
00:25:31.698 --> 00:25:33.242
you can guess how that ended.

397
00:25:33.742 --> 00:25:38.162
and Charles Livingston marries Florence.

398
00:25:38.163 --> 00:25:43.377
which brings me to the final
living descendant of Richard Warren.

399
00:25:44.545 --> 00:25:47.630
[thunderclap. rumbling]

400
00:25:47.631 --> 00:25:51.385
And to my knowledge.
has no clue about their lineage.

401
00:25:52.010 --> 00:25:54.804
Never married. never had children.

402
00:25:54.805 --> 00:26:00.269
which is surprising
because this one was a real beaut.

403
00:26:05.816 --> 00:26:08.610
Miss Widow's Bay. 1959.

404
00:26:14.199 --> 00:26:15.284
So. there's just one?

405
00:26:16.827 --> 00:26:20.413
One-One descendant of Warren
that's still alive?

406
00:26:20.414 --> 00:26:22.082
Just one in the bloodline. and…

407
00:26:23.292 --> 00:26:24.543
and they're old?

408
00:26:29.965 --> 00:26:31.633
[sighs]

409
00:26:45.939 --> 00:26:47.815
What do we know about her health?

410
00:26:47.816 --> 00:26:50.151
- [Patricia] Why are you even asking that?
- You know why.

411
00:26:50.152 --> 00:26:51.403
I hope to hell not.

412
00:26:52.029 --> 00:26:54.406
I mean. how much time
does she even have left?

413
00:26:55.282 --> 00:26:57.201
I can't believe this.

414
00:26:58.368 --> 00:27:00.913
This is a woman
who bakes us birthday cakes.

415
00:27:02.206 --> 00:27:04.040
Who lets your son stay in her home.

416
00:27:04.041 --> 00:27:05.125
Patricia…

417
00:27:06.043 --> 00:27:07.085
[sighs]

418
00:27:07.711 --> 00:27:09.254
…no one wants this.

419
00:27:10.339 --> 00:27:14.343
But there are hundreds of lives at stake.
and one of them is my son.

420
00:27:15.427 --> 00:27:16.929
And that justifies murder?

421
00:27:17.554 --> 00:27:19.555
You can sit there and say all you want.

422
00:27:19.556 --> 00:27:22.099
but you don't know what
the fuck I just saw out there.

423
00:27:22.100 --> 00:27:23.184
This is f…

424
00:27:23.185 --> 00:27:24.186
[chuckles]

425
00:27:25.687 --> 00:27:27.021
This is fucking bad.

426
00:27:27.022 --> 00:27:28.856
If it's done. it needs to be quick.

427
00:27:28.857 --> 00:27:30.525
A gunshot. back of the head.

428
00:27:30.526 --> 00:27:31.776
Oh. my God.

429
00:27:31.777 --> 00:27:34.028
- [Tom] All right. Wyck. come on.
- It's barbaric.

430
00:27:34.029 --> 00:27:36.490
It's the kind thing to do.
She wouldn't see it coming.

431
00:27:39.535 --> 00:27:40.911
[Patricia] Do you hear him?

432
00:27:42.287 --> 00:27:43.997
You're actually considering this?

433
00:27:45.624 --> 00:27:47.084
What would that make you?

434
00:27:49.044 --> 00:27:50.295
What's it say about us?

435
00:27:51.421 --> 00:27:52.505
About this place?

436
00:27:52.506 --> 00:27:55.132
You want Evan to grow up
in a place that does something like that?

437
00:27:55.133 --> 00:27:57.218
He wouldn't have to grow up
in this place at all.

438
00:27:57.219 --> 00:27:58.637
He shouldn't have to.

439
00:27:59.388 --> 00:28:00.973
When she dies. it ends.

440
00:28:02.099 --> 00:28:03.392
She lived a good life.

441
00:28:04.309 --> 00:28:06.436
So. what if she's old? You're old.

442
00:28:07.020 --> 00:28:09.313
Would you want to be killed if it was you
just 'cause you're old?

443
00:28:09.314 --> 00:28:11.525
I was willing to put the gun
in my mouth myself.

444
00:28:12.234 --> 00:28:14.069
- Look. she's not married.
- [Patricia] So?

445
00:28:14.695 --> 00:28:17.446
- I wasn't finished.
- Oh. cool. Keep going then.

446
00:28:17.447 --> 00:28:19.032
She also never had children.

447
00:28:20.826 --> 00:28:22.702
- Well…
- [phone rings]

448
00:28:22.703 --> 00:28:26.205
Thank God I'm not a descendant. or I guess
my throat would already be slit.

449
00:28:26.206 --> 00:28:28.083
This isn't about you.

450
00:28:30.419 --> 00:28:32.087
[ringing continues. stops]

451
00:28:32.713 --> 00:28:35.047
- [static crackling]
- [person speaks indistinctly]

452
00:28:35.048 --> 00:28:36.175
Mitch?

453
00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:38.718
[Mitch. distorted] <i>Oh. God. It's going.</i>

454
00:28:38.719 --> 00:28:41.179
- What-What's going?
- <i>It's all going!</i>

455
00:28:41.180 --> 00:28:43.556
- Mitch. what-what's going?
- [line disconnects]

456
00:28:43.557 --> 00:28:44.766
Mitch? Mitch?

457
00:28:46.768 --> 00:28:47.852
What is it?

458
00:28:47.853 --> 00:28:50.938
I'm not trying to say I told you so.
but you brought families here.

459
00:28:50.939 --> 00:28:53.609
It's been 300 years of hell on this place!

460
00:28:54.318 --> 00:28:55.651
It needs to end.

461
00:28:55.652 --> 00:28:56.986
Don't try to drag it out.

462
00:28:56.987 --> 00:28:59.698
I can make it quick. Peaceful.

463
00:29:01.408 --> 00:29:03.035
You're not doing anything.

464
00:29:04.244 --> 00:29:05.495
What does that mean?

465
00:29:07.122 --> 00:29:08.456
What are you gonna do?

466
00:29:08.457 --> 00:29:10.792
[tense music playing]

467
00:29:17.132 --> 00:29:19.551
[thunderclap. rumbling]
